verbose_text: Supporting this hypothesis, higher expression of eGFP-Vas Delta636-646 enables many more vas 1 embryos to produce pole cells, however the number of pole cells each embryo produces is highly variable, and on average is much lower than that for example in vas 1; egfp-vas Delta15-75, which is expressed at a comparable level (4.3 +/-0.3 versus 9.9 +/-0.2) (supplementary material Fig. S4).
